<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id776f4b2c-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s410eee–1"><num value="410eee–1">§ 410eee–1.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">As used in this subchapter:</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="id776f4b2d-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s410eee–1/1"><num value="1" class="bold">(1)</num><heading class="bold"> Historical park</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The term “historical park” means the Adams National Historical Park established in <ref href="/us/usc/t16/s410eee–2">section 410eee–2 of this title</ref>.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="id776f4b2e-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s410eee–1/2"><num value="2" class="bold">(2)</num><heading class="bold"> Secretary</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The term “Secretary” means the Secretary of the Interior.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id776f4b2f-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/105/342/s3">Pub. L. 105–342, § 3</ref>, <date date="1998-11-02">Nov. 2, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/3201">112 Stat. 3201</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
